    answer: 0,
    explanation: "Ebstein anomaly results from apical displacement of tricuspid valve causing marked right atrial enlargement and severe cardiomegaly.\n\nRadiographs may demonstrate box-shaped heart with variable pulmonary vascularity. Cyanosis commonly occurs due to associated shunts.\n\nTetralogy of Fallot (D) produces boot-shaped heart rather than massive cardiomegaly. Coarctation (E) causes rib notching and aortic abnormalities.\n\n<i>(Core Radiology by Jacob C. Mandell)</i>"
